{"title": "My Monks of Vagabondia", "description": "Before welfare or rehab, what happened to those unfortunates who lost their way, fell through the cracks, were cast off by society? Men such as Andress Floyd and his wife Lillian stepped up. In 1908, the philanthropists converted a mansion in New Jersey into a refuge for homeless men and during the more than 30 years of its operation, more than 100,000 men stayed there until they were able to get back on their feet. In this volume, Floyd has collected 13 diverse true tales of what brought some of the residents to seek succor and enlightenment at the Self-Mastery Colony. - Summary by Lynne Thompson", "duration": 6171, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "12457", "name": "Andress Small Floyd"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/monksofvagabondia_1704_librivox/monksofvagabondia_1704.jpg", "copyright_year": "1913", "genres": ["Social Science (Culture & Anthropology)"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Lynne T"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Lynne T"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Kathrine Engan"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Introductory", "readers": [7756], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/monksofvagabondia_1704_librivox/mymonksofvagabondia_00_floyd_64kb.mp3", "duration": 205}, {"section": 1, "title": "Journey to our Monastery", "readers": [5717], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/monksofvagabondia_1704_librivox/mymonksofvagabondia_01_floyd_64kb.mp3", "duration": 362}, {"section": 2, "title": "Mary and the Baby", "readers": [11131], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/monksofvagabondia_1704_librivox/mymonksofvagabondia_02_floyd_64kb.mp3", "duration": 440}, {"section": 3, "title": "My Problems with Slippery Jim", "readers": [11131], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/monksofvagabondia_1704_librivox/mymonksofvagabondia_03_floyd_64kb.mp3", "duration": 784}, {"section": 4, "title": "O